"(to)v.证明 【英】 v.证明(to declare to be true or genuine) 【记】 at+test(证明)→证明 ，证实 【例】 His success attests his ability. v. 证明, 证实(用签名、誓言、官方职位来证明是真的) 【例】I can attest to the absolute truth of his story 我可以证实他的话是千真万确的. 【记】at一再, test作证明－证明, 证实 【记】at肯定 + 测试； 用测试,实验来肯定地证实 【相关】testify 证明, 作证，testament 遗嘱 attest (v.)  1590s, from Middle French attester (Old French atester, 13c.) ""affirm, attest,"" from Latin attestari ""confirm,"" literally ""bear witness to,"" from ad- ""to"" (see ad-) + testari ""bear witness,"" from testis ""witness"" (see testament). Related: Attested; attesting."
